Ω_2: TRANSITIVE TRIPLES vs TRUE DIMENSION
======================================================================

n=5: dim(Ω_2) - |TT| distribution:
  gap=0: 240 tournaments
  gap=1: 240 tournaments
  gap=2: 280 tournaments
  gap=3: 120 tournaments
  gap=4: 120 tournaments
  gap=5: 24 tournaments

The gap comes from non-TT pairs sharing a non-allowed face.
Non-allowed face (a,c) appears in (a,b,c) when c→a.
If multiple 2-paths share the same non-allowed face,
we get cancellation chains.
